The maturity registration does not change the authority matrix. Marketplace authority also remains unchanged and blocked for payment, settlement, minting, wallet and treasury execution.

## 2026-06-23 - ACS-GOV-02 Future Assessment Authority Gate

Current governance baseline: `L4_READINESS_ADOPTED`; current L-Level `L4_READINESS`; previous L-Level `L4_CANDIDATE`; D-Level `D3+`; L4 Consolidated `NO`.

A future L4 Consolidated assessment must prove, on fresh evidence:

- ACS remains `NON_PRODUCTION`
- ACS remains `EXECUTION_GATED`
- ACS remains `NO_MUTATION_AUTHORITY`
- control-plane and consumer surfaces remain local/config-first/read-only or mock
- no production permission enforcement, state mutation, provisioning, provider execution or hidden integration bypass exists

L4 Consolidated, if ever adopted, would not itself grant production or execution authority. Any authority change requires a separate action-specific governance process.
